<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-794-716  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 794 716.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Oct 23 1989 n338 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software copyright bill gains ground. (House of Representatives'bill will allow state institutions to be sued for infringement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clancy, Heather.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US House of Representatives passes the Copyright RemedyClarification Act, which enables software companies to sue stateagencies for software copyright infringement.andP;  Legal loopholes inthe 11th Constitutional Amendment make state agencies exempt forthe US Copyright Act and the bill is necessary to clarify the law.andO;The bill, which must still be debated and passed in the Senatebefore becoming law, came about after an appeals court overturneda successful copyright infringement case against the University ofCalifornia at Los Angeles.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Statute:   United States Constitution. 11th Amendment (interpretation andconstruction).andO;Topic:     United States. Congress. HouseCopyrightLegal IssuesLegislationSoftware.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>